### forallUnderlyingObjects() {#ab7d7a47641c9fe9bccdfc0265528f8b6}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;AttributorAttributes.cpp&#125;::AAUnderlyingObjectsImpl::forallUnderlyingObjects (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function-ref">function&#95;ref</a>&lt; bool(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &amp;)&gt; Pred, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa/#ac85851126814105f4a92b699293e4141">AA::ValueScope</a> Scope=AA::Interprocedural) const</>}
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
Check <code>Pred</code> on all underlying objects in <code>Scope</code> collected so far.

This method will evaluate <code>Pred</code> on all underlying objects in <code>Scope</code> collected so far and return true if <code>Pred</code> holds on all of them.
